# WM Component Tests — Project Context

## What This Project Is

A data-driven Playwright test framework for testing WaveMaker Studio widget properties. It tests every property for a widget across **Canvas** (Studio DOM) and **Preview** (RN Web Bundle iframe), consuming zero AI tokens at runtime.

## Architecture: 5-Phase Pipeline

```
npx tsx scripts/run-widget-pipeline.ts Button
```

1. **Discover Selectors** (AI Skill, one-time) — Opens Studio, adds widget, inspects Properties/Styles/Events/Device tabs, canvas DOM, preview DOM → outputs `widget-configs/{widget}.config.json`
2. **Generate Test Cases** (AI Skill, one-time) — Reads config, generates test cases with XPath assertions for canvas + preview → outputs `test-cases/{widget}-test-cases.json` → **human reviews**
3. **Canvas Testing** (Playwright, 0 tokens) — Per-case: set property via panel XPath → assert canvas via `@name`/`@widgettype` XPath
4. **Preview Testing** (Playwright, 0 tokens) — Batched: open preview once → assert all via `@data-testid`/`@aria-label` XPath in rn-bundle iframe
5. **Report + Analysis** (deterministic + AI on failure) — JSON/HTML report → S3 upload → auto-analyze failures

## 3 DOM Selector Contexts

- **Context A: Studio Properties Panel** — XPaths to property input fields (text, toggle, dropdown, binding)
- **Context B: Canvas** — XPaths using `@name`, `@widgettype`, CSS classes (e.g., `//button[@name='button1']//span[@class='btn-caption']`)
- **Context C: Preview** — XPaths using `@data-testid`, `@aria-label` in the rn-bundle iframe (e.g., `//div[@data-testid='button1_caption']`)

